The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Putin

 New Delhi, Dec. 4: President Vladimir Putin today clarified that his comments on veto powers for new members of an expanded UN Security Council was misunderstood and said Russia supported India?s case for permanent membership of the Security Council with full veto powers.

 Putin put his views across to Bhairon Singh Shekhawat when the Vice-President called on him. He also explained his position to leader of Opposition L.K. Advani.

 ?He said that he had emphasised the need of retaining the instrument of veto as a means of ensuring the effectiveness of the UN Security Council.... He felt that India as a new member should have the full rights of permanent membership, including veto,? said a government spokesperson. 




